<h2> <span class="mw-headline" id="Notes">Notes</span></h2>
<div class="reflist references-column-count references-column-count-2" style="-moz-column-count: 2; -webkit-column-count: 2; column-count: 2; list-style-type: decimal;">
<ol class="references">
<li id="cite_note-1"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-1">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">People are presumed to be living unless there is reason to believe otherwise. This policy does not apply to people declared <a href="Death_in_absentia" title="Death in absentia">dead <i>in absentia</i></a>.</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-2"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-2">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Jimmy Wales. <a class="external text" href="http://mail.wikimedia.org/pipermail/wikien-l/2006-May/046440.html">"WikiEN-l Zero information is preferred to misleading or false information"</a>, May 16, 2006, and <a class="external text" href="http://mail.wikimedia.org/pipermail/wikien-l/2006-May/046732.html">May 19, 2006</a>; Jimmy Wales. <a class="external text" href="http://wikimania2006.wikimedia.org/wiki/Archives/Jimbo_Keynote">Keynote speech</a>, Wikimania, August 2006.</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-3"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-3">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a href="Wikipedia_Requests_for_arbitration/Rachel_Marsden#WP:BLP_applies_to_all_living_persons_mentioned_in_an_article" title="Wikipedia:Requests for arbitration/Rachel Marsden">Wikipedia:Requests for arbitration/Rachel Marsden</a>: "WP:BLP applies to all living persons mentioned in an article"</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-4"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-4">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">From <a href="Wikipedia_Verifiability#cite_note-3" title="Wikipedia:Verifiability">Wikipedia:Verifiability#cite note-3</a>.</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-What_is_a_conviction.3F-5"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-What_is_a_conviction.3F_5-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Generally, a conviction is secured through court or magisterial proceedings. Accusations, investigations, and arrests on suspicion of involvement do not amount to a conviction. BLPCRIME applies to low-profile individuals and not to well-known individuals, in whose cases <a href="Wikipedia_WELLKNOWN" title="Wikipedia:WELLKNOWN" class="mw-redirect">WP:WELLKNOWN</a> is the appropriate policy to follow.</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-Contradictory_judgements-6"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Contradictory_judgements_6-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">An example of this situation is the <a href="../O._J._Simpson_murder_case" title="O. J. Simpson murder case">O. J. Simpson murder case</a>, where the former footballer <a href="../O._J._Simpson" title="O. J. Simpson">O. J. Simpson</a> was acquitted in 1995 of the crime of murdering <a href="Nicole_Brown_Simpson" title="Nicole Brown Simpson">Nicole Brown Simpson</a> and <a href="Ronald_Goldman" title="Ronald Goldman">Ronald Goldman</a>, but was found liable of their <a href="Wrongful_death" title="Wrongful death" class="mw-redirect">wrongful death</a> in a civil trial two years later.</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-7"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-7">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">See <a href="Wikipedia_Credentials" title="Wikipedia:Credentials" class="mw-redirect">Wikipedia:Credentials</a> and its talk page.</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-8"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-8">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a href="Wikipedia_Requests_for_arbitration/Rangerdude#Mercy" title="Wikipedia:Requests for arbitration/Rangerdude">Wikipedia:Requests for arbitration/Rangerdude#Mercy</a>. Passed 6-0-1.</span></li>
</ol>
